abstract: MADRID, Aug. 31.--There were 3,833 new cases of cholera and 1,248 deaths reported throughout Spain yesterday. In Palencia, Toledo, and Zamora there was an increase in the number of new cases and deaths.

abstract: PIERRE, Dakota, Sept. 15.--All is quiet on Winnebago and Crow Creek Reservations. The recent order sent to Agent Gasman to eject settlers refusing to leave will not be enforced. abstract: Sickness or nausea.  is most commonly relieved by vomiting.
